<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="no-adv">no <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /nəʊ/    美 /noʊ/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[表示否定回答] 不；不是：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Do you smoke? 
你抽烟吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— No, I don’t. 
不，我不抽。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— They shouldn’t drive so fast.
他们开车不该那么快。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— No, it’s really dangerous.
是啊，那样真的很危险。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>[用在形容词、副词比较级前] 根本不；毫不：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She’s feeling no better this morning. 
她今天早晨还是不见好转。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We went no further than the bridge. 
我们走到桥边就不再往前了。</p></div></div>